31-Mar-2010 15:28:00  Exam: NMPET/CT trunk    ORIGINAL REPORT - 31-Mar-2010 15:49:00   Harvest Morningside Memorial Hospital
F-18 FDG PET/CT-scan was performed from the orbits through the upper thighs with CT fusion imaging for attenuation correction and anatomic coregistration only. Urinary drainage catheter was in place. Clinical Indication: Probable rectal cancer. Initial treatment strategy.
Impression: Probable localized rectal cancer without evidence for metastasis.
Findings: Hypermetabolism is seen in the rectum corresponding to increased soft-tissue in the region that is consistent with malignancy. Mild metabolic activity at the anal verge is seen which is probably inflammatory. No hypermetabolic local adenopathy is identified. Normal activity is seen in the abdomen otherwise. Normal
metabolism in the liver. No abnormalities of concern in the chest or neck. Probable arthritis in the left AC joint. Significant incidental findings on the low-dose unenhanced CT fusion images. Bilateral maxillary sinus opacities.

[end section id="20112"]

